{"title_page": "Aion (car brand)", "text_new": "{{infobox brand\n| logo           = [[File:GAC New Energy Logo.png]]\n| name           = Aion\n| type           = [[Automotive industry in China|Automotive]] sub-brand\n| currentowner   =[[GAC Group]] ([[GAC New Energy]] division)\n| origin         = [[China]]\n| introduced     = 2018\n| discontinued   = \n| related        = [[Trumpchi]]\n| markets        = China\n| previousowners = \n| trademarkregistrations = \n| ambassador     = \n| tagline        =\n| website        = {{url|www.gacne.com.cn}}\n}}\n\n'''Aion''' is a Chinese [[electric car]] sub-brand by [[GAC Group|Guangzhou Automobile Corporation]] founded in 2018 to compete in the fast-growing [[China|Chinese]] electric car [[startup company]] market.\n\n==Overview==\n\nAion is an electric car sub-brand by GAC Group's New Energy division for electric, [[hybrid electric vehicle|hybrid]], and [[plug in hybrid electric vehicle|plug-in hybrid]] cars sold under the Aion and [[Trumpchi]] brands. Aion was founded in 2018 and was shown to the public in November with the reveal of the [[Aion S]] at [[Auto Guangzhou]].\n\nAion and Trumpchi's EVs and [[hybrid vehicle|hybrids]] share both the GAC 'G logo' on a blue background and are both sold under the GAC New Energy sub-brand. The electric Trumpchi models won't be sold under the Aion brand as Aion is for original electric cars that are more luxurious and could compete against [[Tesla, Inc.|Tesla]].\n{{clear}}\n\n==Products==\n\n===Current models===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=10%| Model\n!width=30%| Photo \n!width=100%| Specifications\n!| \n|-\n!| [[Aion S|S]]\n|| [[File:GAC Aion S 001.jpg|frameless]]\n||\n'''Body style:''' [[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[C-segment|C]]) [[Compact executive car|Compact executive]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 4\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[CATL]] [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2019\u2013present\n\n'''Revealed:''' November 2018 ([[Auto Guangzhou]])<ref>{{cite web | date = 28 May 2019 | url = https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181119005343/en/GAC-NE-Debuts-Super-E-car-Brand-Aion | title = GAC NE Debuts Super E-car Brand Aion S at Guangzhou International Automobile Exhibition | work = BusinessWire.com | accessdate = 29 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!| [[Aion LX|LX]]\n|| [[File:GAC Aion LX 001.jpg|frameless]]\n||\n\n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Mid-size SUV|Mid-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[CATL]] [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2019 (to commence)\n\n'''Revealed:''' April 2019 ([[Auto Shanghai]])<ref>{{cite web | date = 28 May 2019 | url = https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/gac-new-energy-unveils-electric-suv-aion-lx-with-nedc-range-over-373-miles-300833034.html | title = GAC New Energy Unveils Electric SUV Aion LX With NEDC Range Over 373 Miles | work = PRNewswire.com | accessdate = 29 August 2019}}</ref>\n|| \n|-\n|}\n\n===Upcoming models===\n\nThere are supposedly 11 new vehicles coming from Aion after the LX. The next model is most likely an [[multi-purpose vehicle|MPV]]/[[minivan]] based on the [[Trumpchi Entranze]] concept revealed at the 2019 [[North American International Auto Show]].<ref>{{cite web | date = 28 May 2019 | url = https://insideevs.com/news/342811/gac-to-roll-out-12-new-aion-electric-cars-including-suv-mpv/ | title = GAC To Roll Out 12 New Aion Electric Cars, Including SUV, MPV | website= [[Motorsport_Network#InsideEVs|InsideEVs]] | accessdate = 29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Partnership with NIO==\n\nIn May 2019, GAC and [[NIO (car company)|NIO]] announced they would form a [[joint venture]] electric vehicle brand called Hycan.\n\nHycan later revealed an unnamed electric SUV concept which was essentially an Aion LX with a different front, rear, and wheels.<ref>{{cite web | date = 28 May 2019 | url = https://insideevs.com/news/351718/gac-nio-hycan-brand-concept-bev/ | title = GAC-NIO Introduces Hycan Brand And Concept Electric SUV | work = InsideEVs.com | accessdate = 29 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Sales==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Calendar year\n!LX<ref>http://carsalesbase.com/china-car-sales-data/gac/gac-aion-lx/ GAC Aion LX China Auto Sales Figures at CarSalesBase.com - Retrieved 19 November  2019</ref>\n!S<ref>http://carsalesbase.com/china-car-sales-data/gac/gac-aion-s/ GAC Aion S China Auto Sales Figures at CarSalesBase.com - Retrieved 29 August 2019</ref>\n!V\n!Total\n!Notes\n|-\n|2019\n|1,341\n|32,126\n| -\n|33,467\n|S sales start in May<br/>LX sales start in October\n|-\n|2020\n|301*\n|2,648*\n|0*\n|2,949*\n|Sales drop in early 2020 due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]<br/>*Data as of January 2020\n|}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:GAC_Aion_S_001.jpg| Aion S\nFile:GAC_Aion_S_002.jpg| Aion S\nFile:GAC_Aion_S_003.jpg| Aion S\nFile:GAC_Aion_S_004.jpg| Aion S\nFile:GAC_Aion_LX_001.jpg| Aion LX\nFile:GAC_Aion_LX_002.jpg| Aion LX\nFile:GAC_Aion_LX_003.jpg| Aion LX\nFile:GAC_Aion_LX_004.jpg| Aion LX\n</gallery>\n\n==Other Guangzhou Automobile Corporation brands==\n\n* [[Everus]] ([[Guangqi Honda|GAC-Honda]] electric vehicles)\n* [[Leahead]] ([[GAC Toyota|GAC-Toyota]] electric vehicles)\n* [[Trumpchi]] (GAC passenger cars)\n\n==External links==\n{{url|www.gacne.com.cn|GAC New Energy official website}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:GAC Group divisions and subsidiaries]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Electric vehicle manufacturers of China]]\n[[Category:Luxury motor vehicle manufacturers]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox brand\n| logo           = [[File:GAC New Energy Logo.png]]\n| name           = Aion\n| type           = [[Automotive industry in China|Automotive]] sub-brand\n| currentowner   =[[GAC Group]] ([[GAC New Energy]] division)\n| origin         = [[China]]\n| introduced     = 2018\n| discontinued   = \n| related        = [[Trumpchi]]\n| markets        = China\n| previousowners = \n| trademarkregistratio