{"title_page": "Pawe\u0142 Zagumny", "text_new": "{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Pawe\u0142 Zagumny\n| image          = Pawe\u0142 Zagumny 2010-07-09.jpg\n| image_size     = <!-- Leave this blank for the default size -->\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Pawe\u0142 Lech Zagumny\n| nickname       = ''Guma''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1977|10|18|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Jas\u0142o]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date     = <!-- Use  {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}}   -->\n| death_place    = \n| hometown       = [[Warszawa]], [[Poland]]\n| height         = 2.00 m\n| weight         = \n| spike          = \n| block          = \n| college        = \n| position       = Setter\n| currentclub    = \n| currentnumber  = \n| years          = <br><br>1995\u20131997<br>1997\u20132000<br>2000\u20132003<br>2003\u20132009<br>2009\u20132010<br>2010\u20132015<br>2015\u20132017\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} MKS MDK Warszawa<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Czarni Radom]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} Morze Ba\u0142tyk Szczecin<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sempre Volley]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]]<br> {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]\n| nationalyears  = 1996\u20132014 \n| nationalteam   = {{vb|POL}} <small>(427)</small>\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{POL}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2014 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2006 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 Turkey]] |}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB World League|World League]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 Sofia]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Pawe\u0142 Zagumny''' {{IPAc-pl|AUD|Pl-Pawe\u0142 Zagumny.ogg|'|p|a|w|e|\u0142|-|z|a|'|g|u|m|n|y}} (born 18 October 1977) is a former [[Poland|Polish]] [[volleyball player]], a member of [[Poland men's national volleyball team]] in 1996\u20132014, a participant of the [[Olympic Games]] ([[1996 Summer Olympics|Atlanta 1996]], [[2004 Summer Olympics|Athens 2004]], [[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing 2008]], [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012]]), [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2014 World Champion]], [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 European Champion]], a gold medalist of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 World League]], silver medalist of the [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2006 World Championship]] and [[2011 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2011 World Cup]]. A former sports director of [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO Warszawa]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.sport.pl/siatkowka/1,65101,21528956,siatkowka-pawel-zagumny-dyrektorem-sportowym-onico-azs-politechniki.html | title =Siatk\u00f3wka. Pawe\u0142 Zagumny dyrektorem sportowym ONICO AZS Politechniki Warszawskiej, Stephane Antiga trenerem | date =21 March 2017 | website =sport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> In 2019 he became a president of the Polish Association of Volleyball (Polski Zwi\u0105zek Pi\u0142ki Siatkowej).<ref>{{cite web|url =https://www.przegladsportowy.pl/siatkowka/plusliga/pawel-zagumny-prezesem-pls/265scn6 | title = By\u0142y mistrz \u015bwiata stanie na czele polskiej siatk\u00f3wki. Pawe\u0142 Zagumny zosta\u0142 prezesem PLS! | date =27 January 2019 | website =przegladsportowy.pl | publisher =Kamil Dr\u0105g | author= | access-date = 3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPawe\u0142 Zagumny was born in [[Jas\u0142o]], but he grew up in [[Warszawa]], in [[Ursyn\u00f3w]] district.<ref>{{cite book | author=Pawe\u0142 Zagumny | title = \u017bycie to mecz | publisher = Wydawnictwo Akurat | year = 2015 | url = | pages =13\u201317}}</ref> He is Hanna and Lech Zagumny's son, his father is a former [[volleyball player]] and a coach. Zagumny has a sister, Agnieszka. On July 19, 2003 Zagumny married Oliwia Brochocka-Zagumny. They have two children - a daughter Wiktoria (born 2004) and a son Miko\u0142aj (born 2010).<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.nto.pl/magazyn/reportaz/art/4525337,pawel-zagumny-na-boisku-charyzmatyczny-perfekcyjny-przywodczy,id,t.html | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny. Na boisku charyzmatyczny, perfekcyjny, przyw\u00f3dczy | date =8 October 2012 | website =nto.pl | publisher = | author=Roman St\u0119porowski | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_2005-2006_1.jpg|thumb|Zagumny as [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]] player in season 2005/2006.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_IV_M.jpg|thumb|Zagumny with [[\u0141ukasz Kadziewicz|Kadziewicz]] and [[Micha\u0142 B\u0105kiewicz|B\u0105kiewicz]] during the match of [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] in 2006.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_2006-2007_2.jpg|thumb|During the match [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]] vs [[AZS Cz\u0119stochowa]] in season 2006/2007.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_L\u015a_2012.jpg|thumb|Zagumny before the match of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League 2012]] at [[Spodek]] in [[Katowice]].]]\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nHe began to play in 1992 with MKS MDK Warszawa [[volleyball]] junior [[club (organization)|club]]. His talent was quickly seen and in 1995 at age 18 he was transferred to professional team [[Czarni Radom]], where he played for 2 years. With Zagumny [[Czarni Radom]] club won [[Poland]] [[Championship]] in 1996 and got second place in 1997. Next, he played for Bosman Morze Szczecin for 3 years. In 2000 he was transferred to [[Italy|Italian]] club [[Padova (volleyball)|Edilbasso Padua]], where he stayed for three years. Afterwards he came back to Poland, playing for [[PZU AZS Olsztyn|Mlekpol AZS Olsztyn]]. In 2010 went to Polish club [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]. He achieved with this club two Polish Cups (2013, 2014) and two silver ([[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|2011]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]]) and bronze ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]]) medal of Polish Championship. In April 2015 he announced that he is going to leave [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://sport.wp.pl/kat,33558,title,Zagumny-odchodze-z-Zaksy,wid,17443660,wiadomosc.html?ticaid=11ab93&_ticrsn=3 | title =Zagumny: odchodz\u0119 z Zaksy | date =12 April 2015 | website =wp.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> In May 2015 he signed a contract with [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]].<ref>{{cite web|url =https://onicowarszawa.pl/tv/pawel-zagumny-w-politechnice/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny w Politechnice! | date =27 May 2015 | website =onicowarszawa.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe ended up club career on April 9, 2017 after last match of the season [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|2016\u201317]] as [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] player. The official thanks for his club career was held the day before at [[Torwar Hall]] with almost 5,000 fans.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/31111.html | title =Ostatni warszawski mecz Paw\u0142a Zagumnego | date =8 April 2017 | website =plusliga.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> His shirt number 5 in [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] was reserved until 2022.\n\n===National team===\nIn 2006 he was awarded the best setter of [[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship]] in [[Japan]], where Polish national team won silver medal. In 2007 he was awarded the best setter of [[FIVB World League]] in [[Poland]], [[Katowice]]. In 2008 he was awarded the best setter of [[2008 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympic Games]] in [[Beijing]]. Zagumny was in the Polish squad when the Polish national team won the gold medal of [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2009]], where was awarded Best Setter. On September 14, 2009 he was awarded The [[Order of Polonia Restituta]]. The Order was conferred on the following day by the Prime Minister of Poland, [[Donald Tusk]]. In 2011 the gained silver medal at [[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldCup/2011/Men/viewPressRelease.asp?No=33340&Language=en | title =Poland shoot up World Rankings on back of World Cup silver | date =6 December 2011 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On July 8, 2012 won a gold medal of [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]] in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgary]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35977&Language=en# | title =Poland beat USA to claim first World League title | date =8 July 2012 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35974&Language=en# | title =Poland wins historical gold at the 2012 World League | date =8 July 2012 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On September 21, 2014 won a title of [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Champion 2014]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49500&Language=en#.VCAHAaIu6ho | title =Poland put an end to the reign of Brazil | date =21 September 2014 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49498&Language=en#.VCAG_qIu6ho | title =Poland win second World Championship title at home | date =21 September 2014 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On October 27, 2014 received a state award granted by the Polish President [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]] - [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]] ''for outstanding sports achievements and to promote Polish in the world''. After winning title of 2014 World Champion he announced that the finale was his last match in national team.\n\nOn September 11, 2016 was organized all-star match in [[Katowice]], which was Zagumny's official farewell to Polish national team and its supporters (12,000 fans at [[Spodek]]).<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.polsatsport.pl/wiadomosc/2016-09-11/pawel-zagumny-pozegnal-sie-z-reprezentacja-polski-legenda-odchodzi-po-meczu-gwiazd/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny po\u017cegna\u0142 si\u0119 z reprezentacj\u0105 Polski! Legenda odchodzi po meczu gwiazd | date =11 September 2016 | website =polsatsport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.polsatsport.pl/wiadomosc/2016-09-11/pawel-zagumny-odspiewal-hymn-po-raz-ostatni-wideo/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny od\u015bpiewa\u0142 hymn po raz ostatni! | date =11 September 2016 | website =polsatsport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> In the match Poland vs. the Rest of world took part the most titled and the best players in the history of Polish and world volleyball. Zagumny played 427 matches in Polish national team.\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n====[[CEV Cup]]====\n* [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Cup 2010\u201311|2010/2011]] \u2013 with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n\n====National championship====\n* '''1997/1998''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Polish Championship, with [[Morze Ba\u0142tyk Szczecin]]\n* '''2003/2004''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2003\u201304 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2004/2005''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2004\u201305 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2005/2006''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2005\u201306 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2006/2007''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2006\u201307 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2007/2008''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2007\u201308 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2009/2010''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Greek Cup, with [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]\n* '''2009/2010''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Greek Championship, with [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]\n* '''2010/2011''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2011/2012''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2012/2013''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2012/2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n\n===National team===\n* '''1996''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1996 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship]]\n* '''1997''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[1997 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n* '''2006''' [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n* '''2009''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n* '''2011''' [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n* '''2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n* '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''1997''' [[1997 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2006''' [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2007''' [[Best Player in PlusLiga]]\n* '''2007''' [[2007 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2007''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2008''' [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2011''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2013''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2014''' Polish Cup \u2013 Most Valuable Player\n\n===State awards===\n* '''2006''' [[File:POL Z\u0142oty Krzy\u017c Zas\u0142ugi BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Gold Cross of Merit]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20070230254 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 5 grudnia 2006 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w i odznacze\u0144 | date =5 December 2006 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2009''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Kawalerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Knight's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20100270276 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 14 wrze\u015bnia 2009 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w | date =14 September 2009 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2014''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Oficerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20150000014 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 23 pa\u017adziernika 2014 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w i odznacze\u0144 | date =23 October 2014 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2014''' [[Honorary citizenship]] of [[Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/115/Zagumny-Pawel/ PlusLiga player profile]\n{{s-start}}\n{{S-sports}}\n{{succession box\n| before = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Dawid Murek]]\n| after  = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| title  = [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] captain\n| years  = 2002 \u2013 2004\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| after  = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| title  = [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] captain\n| years  = July 2010 \u2013 October 2010\n}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|FR Yugoslavia}} [[Nikola Grbi\u0107]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Nikola Grbi\u0107]]\n  | title = Best Setter of <br>[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n  | years = [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2006]]\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|BUL}} [[Andrey Zhekov]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Lloy Ball]]\n  | title = Best Setter of <br>[[FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n  | years = [[2007 FIVB Volleyball World League|2007]]\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Ricardo Garcia (volleyball)|Ricardo Garcia]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|BUL}} [[Georgi Bratoev]]\n  | title = Best Setter of <br>[[Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n  | years = [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Beijing 2008]]\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Vadim Khamuttskikh]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Dragan Travica]]\n  | title = Best Setter of <br>[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n  | years = [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009]]\n|}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Commons}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title       = Poland squads\n|bg          = #DC143C\n|fg          = #ffffff\n|bordercolor = #Red\n|list1       =\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2004 Olympics}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2006 FIVB World Championship}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2008 Olympics}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2009 European Championships}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2011 World Cup}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2012 World League}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2012 Olympics}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2014 FIVB World Championship}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zagumny, Pawel}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Jas\u0142o]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Podkarpackie Voivodeship]]\n[[Category:Polish men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Olympic volleyball players of Poland]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Czarni Radom players]]\n[[Category:AZS Warszawa players]]\n[[Category:AZS Olsztyn players]]\n[[Category:ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale players]]\n[[Category:Panathinaikos V.C. players]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Gold Cross of Merit (Poland)]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Order of Polonia Restituta]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Polonia Restituta]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriates in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Italy]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriates in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Greece]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Pawe\u0142 Zagumny\n| image          = Pawe\u0142 Zagumny 2010-07-09.jpg\n| image_size     = <!-- Leave this blank for the default size -->\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Pawe\u0142 Lech Zagumny\n| nickname       = ''Guma''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1977|10|18|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Jas\u0142o]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date     = <!-- Use  {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}}   -->\n| death_place    = \n| hometown       = [[Warszawa]], [[Poland]]\n| height         = 2.00 m\n| weight         = \n| spike          = \n| block          = \n| college        = \n| position       = Setter\n| currentclub    = \n| currentnumber  = \n| years          = <br><br>1995\u20131997<br>1997\u20132000<br>2000\u20132003<br>2003\u20132009<br>2009\u20132010<br>2010\u20132015<br>2015\u20132017\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} MKS MDK Warszawa<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Czarni Radom]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} Morze Ba\u0142tyk Szczecin<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sempre Volley]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]]<br> {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]\n| nationalyears  = 1996\u20132014 \n| nationalteam   = {{vb|POL}} <small>(427)</small>\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{POL}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2014 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2006 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 Turkey]] |}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB World League|World League]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 Sofia]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Pawe\u0142 Zagumny''' {{IPAc-pl|AUD|Pl-Pawe\u0142 Zagumny.ogg|'|p|a|w|e|\u0142|-|z|a|'|g|u|m|n|y}} (born 18 October 1977) is a former [[Poland|Polish]] [[volleyball player]], a member of [[Poland men's national volleyball team]] in 1996\u20132014, a participant of the [[Olympic Games]] ([[1996 Summer Olympics|Atlanta 1996]], [[2004 Summer Olympics|Athens 2004]], [[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing 2008]], [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012]]), [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2014 World Champion]], [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 European Champion]], a gold medalist of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 World League]], silver medalist of the [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2006 World Championship]] and [[2011 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2011 World Cup]]. A former sports director of [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO Warszawa]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.sport.pl/siatkowka/1,65101,21528956,siatkowka-pawel-zagumny-dyrektorem-sportowym-onico-azs-politechniki.html | title =Siatk\u00f3wka. Pawe\u0142 Zagumny dyrektorem sportowym ONICO AZS Politechniki Warszawskiej, Stephane Antiga trenerem | date =21 March 2017 | website =sport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>. In 2019 he became a president of the Polish Association of Volleyball (Polski Zwi\u0105zek Pi\u0142ki Siatkowej).<ref>{{cite web|url =https://www.przegladsportowy.pl/siatkowka/plusliga/pawel-zagumny-prezesem-pls/265scn6 | title = By\u0142y mistrz \u015bwiata stanie na czele polskiej siatk\u00f3wki. Pawe\u0142 Zagumny zosta\u0142 prezesem PLS! | date =27 January 2019 | website =przegladsportowy.pl | publisher =Kamil Dr\u0105g | author= | access-date = 3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPawe\u0142 Zagumny was born in [[Jas\u0142o]], but he grew up in [[Warszawa]], in [[Ursyn\u00f3w]] district.<ref>{{cite book | author=Pawe\u0142 Zagumny | title = \u017bycie to mecz | publisher = Wydawnictwo Akurat | year = 2015 | url = | pages =13\u201317}}</ref> He is Hanna and Lech Zagumny's son, his father is a former [[volleyball player]] and a coach. Zagumny has a sister, Agnieszka. On July 19, 2003 Zagumny married Oliwia Brochocka-Zagumny. They have two children - a daughter Wiktoria (born 2004) and a son Miko\u0142aj (born 2010).<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.nto.pl/magazyn/reportaz/art/4525337,pawel-zagumny-na-boisku-charyzmatyczny-perfekcyjny-przywodczy,id,t.html | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny. Na boisku charyzmatyczny, perfekcyjny, przyw\u00f3dczy | date =8 October 2012 | website =nto.pl | publisher = | author=Roman St\u0119porowski | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_2005-2006_1.jpg|thumb|Zagumny as [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]] player in season 2005/2006.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_IV_M.jpg|thumb|Zagumny with [[\u0141ukasz Kadziewicz|Kadziewicz]] and [[Micha\u0142 B\u0105kiewicz|B\u0105kiewicz]] during the match of [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] in 2006.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_2006-2007_2.jpg|thumb|During the match [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]] vs [[AZS Cz\u0119stochowa]] in season 2006/2007.]]\n[[File:Pawe\u0142_Zagumny_L\u015a_2012.jpg|thumb|Zagumny before the match of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League 2012]] at [[Spodek]] in [[Katowice]].]]\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nHe began to play in 1992 with MKS MDK Warszawa [[volleyball]] junior [[club (organization)|club]]. His talent was quickly seen and in 1995 at age 18 he was transferred to professional team [[Czarni Radom]], where he played for 2 years. With Zagumny [[Czarni Radom]] club won [[Poland]] [[Championship]] in 1996 and got second place in 1997. Next, he played for Bosman Morze Szczecin for 3 years. In 2000 he was transferred to [[Italy|Italian]] club [[Padova (volleyball)|Edilbasso Padua]], where he stayed for three years. Afterwards he came back to Poland, playing for [[PZU AZS Olsztyn|Mlekpol AZS Olsztyn]]. In 2010 went to Polish club [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]. He achieved with this club two Polish Cups (2013, 2014) and two silver ([[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|2011]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]]) and bronze ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]]) medal of Polish Championship. In April 2015 he announced that he is going to leave [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://sport.wp.pl/kat,33558,title,Zagumny-odchodze-z-Zaksy,wid,17443660,wiadomosc.html?ticaid=11ab93&_ticrsn=3 | title =Zagumny: odchodz\u0119 z Zaksy | date =12 April 2015 | website =wp.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> In May 2015 he signed a contract with [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]].<ref>{{cite web|url =https://onicowarszawa.pl/tv/pawel-zagumny-w-politechnice/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny w Politechnice! | date =27 May 2015 | website =onicowarszawa.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe ended up club career on April 9, 2017 after last match of the season [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|2016\u201317]] as [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] player. The official thanks for his club career was held the day before at [[Torwar Hall]] with almost 5,000 fans.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/31111.html | title =Ostatni warszawski mecz Paw\u0142a Zagumnego | date =8 April 2017 | website =plusliga.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> His shirt number 5 in [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska|ONICO AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] was reserved until 2022.\n\n===National team===\nIn 2006 he was awarded the best setter of [[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship]] in [[Japan]], where Polish national team won silver medal. In 2007 he was awarded the best setter of [[FIVB World League]] in [[Poland]], [[Katowice]]. In 2008 he was awarded the best setter of [[2008 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympic Games]] in [[Beijing]]. Zagumny was in the Polish squad when the Polish national team won the gold medal of [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2009]], where was awarded Best Setter. On September 14, 2009 he was awarded The [[Order of Polonia Restituta]]. The Order was conferred on the following day by the Prime Minister of Poland, [[Donald Tusk]]. In 2011 the gained silver medal at [[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldCup/2011/Men/viewPressRelease.asp?No=33340&Language=en | title =Poland shoot up World Rankings on back of World Cup silver | date =6 December 2011 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On July 8, 2012 won a gold medal of [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]] in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgary]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35977&Language=en# | title =Poland beat USA to claim first World League title | date =8 July 2012 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35974&Language=en# | title =Poland wins historical gold at the 2012 World League | date =8 July 2012 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On September 21, 2014 won a title of [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Champion 2014]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49500&Language=en#.VCAHAaIu6ho | title =Poland put an end to the reign of Brazil | date =21 September 2014 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49498&Language=en#.VCAG_qIu6ho | title =Poland win second World Championship title at home | date =21 September 2014 | website =fivb.org | publisher =FIVB | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> On October 27, 2014 received a state award granted by the Polish President [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]] - [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]] ''for outstanding sports achievements and to promote Polish in the world''. After winning title of 2014 World Champion he announced that the finale was his last match in national team.\n\nOn September 11, 2016 was organized all-star match in [[Katowice]], which was Zagumny's official farewell to Polish national team and its supporters (12,000 fans at [[Spodek]]).<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.polsatsport.pl/wiadomosc/2016-09-11/pawel-zagumny-pozegnal-sie-z-reprezentacja-polski-legenda-odchodzi-po-meczu-gwiazd/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny po\u017cegna\u0142 si\u0119 z reprezentacj\u0105 Polski! Legenda odchodzi po meczu gwiazd | date =11 September 2016 | website =polsatsport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.polsatsport.pl/wiadomosc/2016-09-11/pawel-zagumny-odspiewal-hymn-po-raz-ostatni-wideo/ | title =Pawe\u0142 Zagumny od\u015bpiewa\u0142 hymn po raz ostatni! | date =11 September 2016 | website =polsatsport.pl | publisher = | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref> In the match Poland vs. the Rest of world took part the most titled and the best players in the history of Polish and world volleyball. Zagumny played 427 matches in Polish national team.\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n====[[CEV Cup]]====\n* [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Cup 2010\u201311|2010/2011]] \u2013 with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n\n====National championship====\n* '''1997/1998''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Polish Championship, with [[Morze Ba\u0142tyk Szczecin]]\n* '''2003/2004''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2003\u201304 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2004/2005''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2004\u201305 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2005/2006''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2005\u201306 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2006/2007''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2006\u201307 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2007/2008''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2007\u201308 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n* '''2009/2010''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Greek Cup, with [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]\n* '''2009/2010''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Greek Championship, with [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos Athens]]\n* '''2010/2011''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2011/2012''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2012/2013''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2012/2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n* '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n\n===National team===\n* '''1996''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1996 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship]]\n* '''1997''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[1997 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n* '''2006''' [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n* '''2009''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n* '''2011''' [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n* '''2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n* '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''1997''' [[1997 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2006''' [[2006 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2007''' [[Best Player in PlusLiga]]\n* '''2007''' [[2007 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2007''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2008''' [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2009''' [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2011''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2013''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2014''' Polish Cup \u2013 Most Valuable Player\n\n===State awards===\n* '''2006''' [[File:POL Z\u0142oty Krzy\u017c Zas\u0142ugi BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Gold Cross of Merit]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20070230254 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 5 grudnia 2006 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w i odznacze\u0144 | date =5 December 2006 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2009''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Kawalerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Knight's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20100270276 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 14 wrze\u015bnia 2009 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w | date =14 September 2009 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2014''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Oficerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]<ref>{{cite web|url =http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP20150000014 | title =Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 23 pa\u017adziernika 2014 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w i odznacze\u0144 | date =23 October 2014 | website =sejm.gov.pl | publisher =ISAP | author= | access-date = 7 February 2018}}</ref>\n* '''2014''' [[Honorary citizenship]] of [[Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/115/Zagumny-Pawel/ PlusLiga player profile]\n{{s-start}}\n{{S-sports}}\n{{succession box\n| before = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Dawid Murek]]\n| after  = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| title  = [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] captain\n| years  = 2002 \u2013 2004\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| after  = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| title  = [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] captain\n| years  = July 2010 \u2013 October 2010\n}}\n{{s-